    <string name="update_message">
    Hey there!\n\n
    This update finally fixes the bug where offline comics have black bars on the bottom (thanks to Mason Cooper on Github!).
    For the changes to take effect, you will have to manually disable offline mode in the settings and then enable it again. \n\n
    Thanks for using the app!
    </string>

    <string name="scoped_storage_message">
    Hey there!\n\n
    Up to now, Easy Xkcd used a custom folder to store offline data (both comics and What-if articles).
    Starting from Android 11, apps are required to keep their data only in predefined app-specific directories.
    While this is not a strict requirement for Android 9 or lower (Android 10 is sort of a special case),
    for the sake of consistency I have decided to keep the handling of offline data consistent across Android versions.
    This also has the benefit that the permissions READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE and WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAGE won\'t
    be necessary anymore and will be removed in a future update. \n\n
    In preparation for this transition, the app will need to move your existing
    offline data to a directory that is compatible with Android 11\'s scoped storage concept. Currently, the
    data is stored in \"%1$s\", it will be moved to \"%2$s\" (this corresponds to external storage).
    If you prefer internal storage (%3$s), you can change this in the app\'s settings afterwards.\n\n

    If you have any problems, please send me a mail (easyxkcd@gmail.com) or submit an issue on Github.
    As always, thanks for using the app!
